#@``.....#  <- I am at @. To my east is ``, so two boulders.
##.......#
##########
```

I first tried the obvious, pushing east. Got the ""in vain"" message – that means I'm facing a wall or two boulders in front of me, which makes sense looking at the map. I can't push two boulders at once. So, I need to get *around* them.

Let's trace some coordinates to be certain and not assume!  Boulders are at (36, 12), (37, 12). Row 13: `#@``.....#` - I am at 35, and 36, 37 are boulders. Now, from the map, Row 12 is `#.`##.{..#` and then, from that line, I can see that (36,12) is a `.`, (37,12) is '#'.  So, moving north to (35, 12) *seems* like a possible route. But wait, if I go north to (35, 12), the boulder at (36,12) and the wall at (37,12) are going to be a problem. This won't work.

