**Strategic Planning**

So, the boulder at (39,10) is a red herring. It's stuck! I now focus on the other three: (36,12), (36,13), and (37,13). My strategy has to evolve around clearing paths, which involves strategically moving the boulders to create clear paths to their target locations.

I can move (36,12), which is at (36,12). The next boulder in line is (36,13). I can push east to (37,13), but that's occupied. The only option is to move that east most boulder. And now, I must move (37,13). I must move around! I see the path around to the bottom! I can make a right, around, then push a boulder!

