**Pathfinding and Movement Strategies**

The standard Sokoban principles apply: I can only move by pushing one boulder at a time, and I can't move diagonally. This significantly constrains movement. I need to avoid dead-end situations where boulders block further progress.

**Detailed Movement Planning & Tracing**

My focus needs to be clearing the way to push boulders onto fountains.

